\begin{spell}[S-6]{Echosense}
d531 9
a539 28
\sItem{Range}{Self}
\sItem{Duration}{30 minutes + 30 / Rank.}
\sItem{Experience Multiple}{150}
\sItem{Base Chance}{25\%}
\sItem{Resist}{May not be resisted}
\sItem{Target}{Self}
\sItem{Storage}{Potion}
\emph{Effect:} The Adept is able to sense sounds as they rebound from
objects.  These sounds must be generated by the Adept by physical
means, either vocally, or by means of an instrument. Using this spell
the Adept can ``see'' even in total darkness (such as a Rank 20
magical Darkness), or with eyes shut or blinded. However, Echosense
is not sight. Images are unclear and blurred, and recognition is
difficult, especially at low Ranks, and whilst it is possible to
target spells using Echosense, the Adept may not be able to tell
friend from foe. The range of the Echosense is 30 feet (+ 5 / Rank).
\end{spell}

