\subsubsection{Jeering and Taunting Song (G-6)}
d222 4
a225 4
\emph{Range:} 15 feet + 15/rank \\
\emph{Duration:} 10 seconds + 10/rank \\
\emph{Experience multiple:} 200 \\
\emph{Base Chance:} 25\% \\
d227 2
a228 30
\emph{Target:} Sentient entity \\
\emph{Storage:} Invested, Ward, Magical Trap \\
\emph{Effects:}
\end{spelldesc}

This spell causes a song or poem to be heard by the target,
detailing the target's shortcomings and inflicting general abuse,
insults and mockery. A target that fails to resist may be
embarrassed, shocked, humiliated, indignant or infuriated as
appropriate to their personality. Whatever the emotional effect,
the character is distracted, and may only take pass actions for
the duration of the spell or until the target successfully makes
a check against 1 \x willpower. This check is made at the end of
the pulse following the pulse in which the spell is cast and
every pulse thereafter. The target must be able to understand the
Adept in order for the spell to have any effect. (It will not
work in the area of a Confusion of Tongues spell or on non-
sentients.)

