The Adept shrieks in an unnatural and piercing fashion, creating
ethereal dissonances that can destroy objects. The Adept may
affect an object of no more than 0.5 pounds (+0.5/Rank).
Additionally, the Rank of this spell determines what material may
be destroyed:
Rank 0-2  glass, mirror
     3-4  ceramics
     5-6  crystals
     7-8  stone
     9-10 gems
     11-12     bone or ivory
     13-14     hard metal (iron)
     15-16     soft metal (bronze)           
     17-20     wood

An object has the resistance of its possessor. If the object is
not in the possession of any entity, it has a base resistance of
zero. Crafted objects and those made of precious materials
receive bonuses to their resistance rolls, as detailed below.
Permanently magical items are immune to the effects of this
spell. These bonuses are cumulative.
     Crafting modifier:  2 \x Artisan Rank
     Material Modifiers:
     Silver              + 5 \%
     Gold                +10 \%
     Truesilver          +15 \%
     Precious gems, etc. +20 \%.
(The GM should only apply the least of the material modifiers to
the resistance roll).
