\subsubsection{Implanting Songs (Q-1)}
d358 4
a361 4
\emph{Range:} 10 feet + 10/rank \\
\emph{Duration (of sound sequence):} 10 seconds + 10/rank \\
\emph{Experience multiple:} 250 \\
\emph{Base Chance:} 25\% \\
a364 1
\emph{Materials:} None \\
a366 2
\emph{Storage:} Special \\
\emph{Effects:}
d368 14
a381 18

This ritual implants a sequence of sounds (which may be words,
spoken or sung) into an object or area. The Adept may determine
how it is triggered, based on a simple visual or aural cue, such
as an object being picked up, or a boundary being crossed. Sounds
implanted in an object are triggered by a tactile cue, usually
simply the object being touched. The sound will be emitted every
time the object or area is triggered, up to a number of times
equal to one + rank. The volume of the sound produced may not
exceed that of loud ringing of bells and may be heard at that
volume everywhere within the range. 
If a general knowledge counter-spell of this college is
successfully cast over the object or within the area the ritual
is dissipated. Otherwise it dissipates after a period of 1 week
+ 1 week/rank has passed. (At rank 20 the implanted sound is
permanent until dissipated). If the ritual backfires the sounds
are triggered immediately and will repeat rank times, or until
counter-spelled. 
d388 3
a390 3
\emph{Experience multiple:} 200 \\
\emph{Base Chance:} 30\% + 5/Rank \\
\emph{Resist:} Cannot be resisted \\
d392 3
a394 6
\emph{Cast Time:} One hour \\
\emph{Materials:} None \\
\emph{Actions:} Meditation \\
\emph{Concentration Check:} Normal \\
\emph{Storage:} None \\
\emph{Effects:}
d396 11
a406 13

At the completion of this ritual the adept will enter a trance,
during which the adept will recite a legend or story relating to
the bard's current location, to an object held in the bard's
hands, or to an entity the Adept is touching. If no such story
exists, or the ritual fails then the adept will recite some
amusing but trivial song. If the ritual backfires the legend will
be false. The amount of information received is related to the
Bard's rank with this ritual. If the gamemaster prefers this may
be played as obtaining an answer to 3 (+1/3 ranks) short
questions related to the location, object or entity which will
be answered in "legendary" terms. This ritual may not be repeated
on a given target until a week has passed.
