\subsubsection{Charm Entity (S-1)}
d413 3
a415 3
\emph{Range:} 50 feet + 5/rank \\
\emph{Duration:} 1 hour + 1/rank \\
\emph{Experience multiple:} 300 \\
d417 18
a434 18
\emph{Resist:} Passive and Active \\
\emph{Target:} Living entity \\
\emph{Storage:} Potion, Invested, Ward, Magical Trap \\
\emph{Effects:}
\end{spelldesc}
The Adept can influence the actions of an entity who fails to resist,
provided that the target can hear and understand the Bard. The target
will see the Adept as his true friend and will readily accept most
suggestions emanating from them. Any suggestion that is not directly
and obviously inimical to the target's interests (as defined by the
gamemaster, but usually limited to actions that would be injurious or
fatal) will be acted upon 90\% of the time. The Adept may only ensure
100\% compliance with a request by making it an order in which case
the target makes an immediate Resistance Check. Any suggestion that
would lead to the target's injury or death results in an immediate
Resistance Check. If successful the spell is broken.  Otherwise, the
target accepts the order and will carry it out faithfully for the
duration of the spell.
