\subsubsection{Dance of Swords (S-4)}

\begin{spelldesc}
\emph{Range:} 5ft + 5/rank \\
\emph{Duration:} 30 minutes + 30/rank \\
\emph{Experience multiple:} 150 \\
\emph{Base Chance:} 30\% \\
\emph{Resist:} May not be resistedne \\
d500 1
a500 2
\emph{Storage:} Potion \\
\emph{Effects:}
d502 12
a513 32
While under the effect of this spell, the target may cavort and leap
with surpassing grace and extravagance by evoking the magic of the
dance. The target may walk and act in all ways normally, however, when
they enter combat they may "dance" adding 2 (+2/Rank) to their Defence
provided they move at least 1 hex each round. If the target is
unwillingly confined to a single hex (by the effect of melee zones for
example) the target must halve the defence bonus due to this spell. If
the target is unable to move freely (in close combat or stunned) then
no defence bonus is awarded. The target may always subtract the Rank
of this spell from the dice roll for any Agility Check solely
involving Agility (eg. avoid knockdown, leaping pits etc).


\subsubsection{Echosense Spell (S-5)}

\begin{spelldesc}
\emph{Range:} self only \\
\emph{Duration:} 30 minutes + 30/rank. \\
\emph{Experience multiple:} 150 \\
\emph{Base Chance:} 30\% \\
\emph{Resist:} none \\
\emph{Target:} self only. \\
\emph{Storage:} Potion.  \\
\emph{Effects:}
\end{spelldesc}
The adept is enabled to sense sounds as they rebound from
objects. These sounds must be generated by the adept by physical
means, vocally, or by means of an instrument. Using this spell the
adept can "see" in total darkness (such as a Rank 20 magical
Darkness), even with eyes shut or blinded. However, echosense is not
sight. Images are unclear and blurred, and recognition is difficult,
especially at low rank. The range of echosense is 30ft + 5/rank.
