\emph{Experience multiple:} 400 \\
\emph{Base Chance:} MA + 4/Rank \\
\emph{Cast Time:} Special (at least 1 hour) \\
\emph{Resist:} May not be resistedne \\
\emph{Target:} Non-sentient entities of nominated type \\
d779 2
a780 4
\emph{Actions:} Play instrument and walk through area \\
\emph{Concentration Check:} None \\
\emph{Storage:} None \\
\emph{Effects:}
d782 14
a795 15
The Adept nominates a type of non-sentient entity which normally forms
swarms, packs or herds (eg. rats, locusts) at the start of this
ritual. The size of the entity which can be affected is dependant on
rank. Up to rank 5 entities less than 1lb in weight can be affected,
between rank 5 and rank 10 entities less than 10lb, between rank 10
and rank 15, entities less than 100lb, at rank 16 and above entities
greater than 100lb. The Adept then begins to play a tune which has a
compelling effect on all entities of the target type. As the Adept
walks through the target area these entities come out and begin to
follow the Adept growing into a horde. At the end of an hour or more
of walking the Adept leads the horde out of the area, and then gives a
single command to the horde. The wording of this command may not
exceed 1 word + 1/3 full ranks. The command will be obeyed for a
period of 1 hour + 1 hour per rank.

a796 1
